    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Viewers for full-plate Daguerreotype stereo pairs, designed and patented by Southworth &amp; Hawes, ca. 1853. A large cabinet mounted on a cast-iron base could display ten stereo pairs in succession by means of a crank.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
